	(lib_symbols)
	(text_box "POWER MANAGEMENT NOTES:\n- The Power Budget Breakdown\n  - The LM66100 is rated for a maximum continuous current (I MAX) of 1.5 A across an input voltage range of 1.5 V to 5.5 V. Let's add up the peak consumption of your components on the target 3.3V power domain:\n  - STM32H7S3I8T6: Running at its maximum core clock of 600 MHz under a heavy DSP/graphics load, the MCU itself will draw roughly 150 mA to 220 mA.\n  - AS4C32M8SA-7TCN (256Mb SDRAM): High-speed continuous burst reading/writing for frame-buffering the LCD draws a maximum peak current of around 90 mA to 120 mA.\n  - MX30LF1G18AC-TI (1Gb SLC NAND Flash): During an active page program or block erase sequence, it draws a peak of roughly 30 mA.\n  - ILI9488 LCD Module: The controller logic itself only draws a tiny few milliamps, but the LED Backlight panel is power-hungry. At full brightness, a standard 3.5-inch panel draws between 90 mA to 150 mA.\nTotal Worst-Case Peak Consumption:\nTotal Current≈220 mA+120 mA+30 mA+150 mA=520 mA"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
